==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Denary
<hw>Den"a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>denarius</ets>. See 2d <er>Denier</er>.]</ety> <def>Containing ten;
tenfold; proceeding by tens; <as>as, the <ex>denary</ex>, or decimal,
scale</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Denary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Denary
<hw>Den"a*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The number ten; a
division into ten.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A coin; the Anglicized form of
<xex>denarius</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Udall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>denationalisation</ent>⟦br⟧
